article.description: — Tyler Whitney-Sidney's 21 points helped Lehigh defeat Holy Cross 76-58 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Whitney-Sidney scores 21 as Lehigh knocks off Holy Cross
article.linkText: Whitney-Sidney scores 21 as Lehigh knocks off Holy Cross
article.story:
BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- — Tyler Whitney-Sidney's 21 points helped Lehigh defeat Holy Cross 76-58 on Wednesday night.

Whitney-Sidney also added six rebounds for the Mountain Hawks (8-8, 3-2 Patriot League). Evan Taylor added 12 points while going 4 of 15 from the floor, including 3 for 8 from distance, and 1 for 3 from the line, and he also had seven rebounds. Dominic Parolin recorded nine points and finished 4 of 9 from the field.

Gerrale Gates led the way for the Crusaders (6-12, 3-2) with 24 points, 11 rebounds and two blocks. Will Batchelder added 15 points for Holy Cross. In addition, Jade Tse finished with six points and four assists.

NEXT UP

Both teams next play Saturday. Lehigh hosts American while Holy Cross visits Lafayette.

------
